WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
Forgotten Domain — A Case Study in DNS Security

2
00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:12.000
A domain registered for ten years with no published mail policy is not dormant — it is exposed.

3
00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:20.000
Without SPF, DMARC, and a Null MX record, any domain becomes a free spoofing vector.

4
00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:28.000
Reputation systems do not distinguish between negligence and compromise. They only see the absence of published policy.

5
00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:36.000
Three DNS records separate protection from impersonation: SPF -all, DMARC reject, and Null MX.

6
00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:42.000
If a domain sends no mail, publish these records. Silence is not protection.
